$ ctetra4_free_thermal.bdf
$ Six CTETRA4 (Kuhn cube) — free thermal expansion with zero stress
$
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      same minimal set as chexa8_free_thermal — all compatible with
$           the free-expansion field u = alpha*dT*x, v = alpha*dT*y, w = alpha*dT*z
$
$ Expected (alpha*dT = 1e-3):
$   Top-face nodes (z=1): w = 1e-3 m
$   Node 6 at (1,0,1): u = 1e-3 m
$   Node 7 at (1,1,1): u = 1e-3 m, v = 1e-3 m
$   Stress ≈ 0 in all six tetrahedra (CST is exact for linear fields)
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTETRA4 FREE THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: unit cube
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
$ Material: alpha = 1e-5 /°C
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSOLID,1,1
$ 6-tet Kuhn decomposition
CTETRA,1,1,1,2,3,7
CTETRA,2,1,1,5,6,7
CTETRA,3,1,1,4,8,7
CTETRA,4,1,2,1,6,7
CTETRA,5,1,5,1,8,7
CTETRA,6,1,4,1,3,7
$ Minimal BCs (compatible with free-expansion field)
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C on all nodes
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
TEMP,1,5,100.0
TEMP,1,6,100.0
TEMP,1,7,100.0
TEMP,1,8,100.0
ENDDATA
